    {
        "content": "<p>It seems that lean4 defines <code>0 - 1 = 0</code><br>\nI found this theorem in <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Init/Data/Nat/Basic.html#Nat.zero_sub\">docs#Nat.zero_sub</a></p>",
        "id": 481440247,
        "sender_full_name": "Gaolei He",
        "timestamp": 1731139935
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The substraction of two nat has to be a nat, so it is truncated at 0, ie if a &lt;= b then a-b=0</p>",
